# Parser Regression Test Fixtures
# Each line is a JSON object with test case data
# Lines starting with # are comments
#
# Format:
# {"content": "message text", "expected": {...}, "category": "...", "notes": "..."}
#
# Expected fields:
# - ideas_count: exact number or [min, max] range
# - min_ideas: minimum number of ideas expected
# - not_noise: true if message should produce ideas
# - instruments: expected instrument types
# - primary_symbols: expected symbols (null for sector/macro)
# - labels_any: at least one of these labels should appear
# - labels_all: all of these labels must appear
# - skip_quality_check: true to skip short-idea validation
#
# To capture real responses, run with --capture-fixtures flag (when implemented)

{"content": "Bought 100 shares of AAPL at 185", "expected": {"ideas_count": 1, "not_noise": true, "primary_symbols": ["AAPL"], "labels_any": ["TRADE_EXECUTION"]}, "category": "trade_execution", "notes": "Simple buy order"}
